identificationRemarks: An easy nomenclatural trap: the plant in California and east to the Rockies should be H. parviFOLIA (Little-LEAF or common alum-root), not H. parviFLORA (Small-flowered alum-root). Life was easier when plants in our area were segregated as Heuchera duranii. A note in Flora of North America: "The specific epithet, parviflora, is similar to that of another species, Heuchera parvifolia, but these two species are distinct and have different legitimate names"" (http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=242416652). H. parviflora is an eastern species: var. parviflora is in ""southern Appalachian Mountains and Interior Plateau east of the Mississippi River and in Missouri"" (http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=250065938). Var. puberula is ""mostly restricted to the Ozark Mountains of Arkansas and Missouri, plus sites in central Kentucky and southern Indiana"" (http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=250065939). H. parvifolia is a western species, found in ""Alta., Sask.; Ariz., Calif., Colo., Idaho, Mont., Nev., N.Mex., Utah, Wyo."" (http://www.efloras.org/florataxon.aspx?flora_id=1&taxon_id=250065974)."

eventRemarks: (Glendo in Platte Counry) Medicine Bow National Forest: Laramie Mountains: La Bonte Canyon: vicinity of Curtis Gulch Campground. (From end of WY Hwy 91: 3.0 road mi S to jct of Counry Road 24 [=Cold Spring Road] and County Road 16 [=Old Ft Fetterman Road], 12.85 road mi on County Road 16 to La Bonte Road [=FSR 658], then 3.45 road mi to site.) Montane Juniperus scopulorum-Pinus flexilis-Pinus ponderosa-Pseudotsuga menziesii forest on steep, rocky, S and SW-facing slopes above confluence of Curtis Gulch and La Bonte Creek, with shrubby understory dominated by Artemisia tridentata, Juniperus communis, Physocarpus monogynus, Populus tremuloides and Purshia tridentata, and along creek by Acer glabrum, Cornus sericea, Prunus virginiana and Rosa nutkana. Tall granite cliffs at top of slope with abundant boulders on slopes below; coarse sandy soil.
